{
  "texts": [
    "This balance makes the z-σ threshold a more reliable and versatile choice for handling datasets with varying levels of contamination.",
    "Adaptive and Aggressive RejectionTo effectively suppress the influence of anomalous samples throughout training, we adopt an adaptive rejection strategy that evolves with the model's learning progress.",
    "In the early phase, when the model is still unstable, we apply a hard rejection method to ensure that training focuses on the most trustworthy normal samples.",
    "This stabilizes optimization and prevents the model from being misled by potential anomalies.",
    "As training advances and the anomaly scoring becomes more reliable, we progressively combine hard and soft rejection schemes."
  ]
}